English:
Nowadays, however, several emerging countries (if not all) are benefiting from years of substantial effort to reduce their financial vulnerability from the accumulation of large foreign-exchange reserves. They have also paid back a significant part of their foreign debt, and converted much of the rest into easier-to-manage domestic liabilities.

German:
