English:
Putin continues to deny that Russia’s financial problems were caused by his war in Georgia, and that the central bank needed more than a month to provide strong financial injections. But it was already too late, because the liquidity problem had become a matter of solidarity. Russian stocks actually look attractive, but Putin scared the foreigners by over-bundling them with insults, and Russian investors have no money. Each explanation erodes Putin’s political profile.

German:
