English:
From Morgan Stanley’s Stephen Roach or Paul Krugman of Princeton, economists like the US Federal Reserve’s governors, the leading bodies of the European Central Bank, and economic specialists throughout Japan, are worrying about deflation. Their thinking retraces the economic thought of fifty years ago, when economists concluded that deflation should be avoided at all costs.

German:
