English:
The fourth tier comprises countries that trail the rest – the world’s most advanced economies, with roughly one billion people. They continue to stagnate or develop backward. Most are in sub-Saharan Africa. These “railroad runners” are widely isolated from the global economy and face critical development problems.

German:
