English:
It did. The cheerleaders broke out and became lame. Romney let it grow. The crowd cracked up and gave the point: “Let the planet grow.” That was perhaps the most dignified and sad moment in a painful election campaign. In the history now written about humanity’s efforts to preserve a living planet, that moment was crafted to seek out unsterile traurious fame.

German:
