English:
Walnuts cannot be killed humanely – they are too big, and even with a snuff harp, it is difficult to get the Wal right. Walfowl also do not want to use too much fuel, because it would burn the Wal in pieces. So the whole process is to preserve valuable meat and oil. So harpooned Wale dies typically slowly and poorly.

German:
