English:
In Japan, the QL may have contributed to the delay in economic reforms and restructurings, weakening longer-term economic growth and exacerbated fiscal tightening. In the US, it failed to avert the downturn between 2008 and 2011. American inflation is likely to be higher in 2011 than in 2007. In the United Kingdom, growth is slower and inflation much higher. And the QL in these countries also fueled asset bubbles in the global economy.

German:
