English:
Moore became suspicious when UCLA’s cancer specialists repeatedly tested his blood, skin, and sperm for seven years. When Moore discovered that he was a patient number 4.438.032 in 1984, he sued for malpractice and property damages. His physician claimed that Moore had averted his interest in body parts by signing a general consent form. But Moore felt violated in his integrity, and believed that his body had been exploited, and that his tissue had been used to make discoveries.

