English:
The spread of global value chains that integrate hundreds of millions of workers in developing countries into the global economy, together with new labor-saving technologies, imply little chance of a change in wages’ costs. Likewise, the market for long-term bonds are extremely low inflationary expectations (although they are higher in the case of looming sovereign defaults or the risk of re-mining, as in southern Europe, but this has nothing to do with inflation). Moreover, the debt-deleveraging that has been running since the implosion of financial structures in 2008 could be easier if inflation is slightly higher for a long time, a debate that the International Monetary Fund fought a year ago.

German:
