English:
This effort is particularly important in cosmology, where a peaceful coexistence between relativity, which is the theory of attraction, and quantum theory is necessary to understand the origins of the universe. During the early moments after the universe’s creation by the urn, 12 billion years ago, the universe was very small and dense; the laws of nature were, in fact, limited to a type of particles and only a force. As a result, unifying relativity and quantum theory is necessary in order to understand the first moments of creation, when other parts and forces have developed.

