English:
The China-US relationship resembles that of a shipping house to a less solvent client. The country with the largest population in the world is the largest foreign creditor of the US government and government-sponsored companies like Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac. China’s official foreign reserves, which total more than $2.5 trillion, are invested in two-tiered current-account surpluses and capital in dollars, and are largely invested in dollar bonds.

German:
