English:
Foreign aid is no substitute for insurance. Favorites inspire and enchant us, but they are often reassuring. You don’t want to rely on them. Indeed, countries often seem to be guided primarily by their leaders’ reflections on the external impact of the aid they are providing. Favorites respond to events that attract all attention, and are often neglecting less sensational catastrophes.

German:
