English:
But paying for and providing these vaccines to the most vulnerable citizens in low-income countries poses a major challenge. Although the World Health Organization has since 1992 recommended that HBV vaccination be included in routine immunization programs, the high cost initially hindered its use in some developing countries. More recently, the same problem threatened the introduction of HPV vaccines. But the GAVI Alliance has intervened to ensure that the cost of hepatitis B is no longer a barrier, and that the HPV problem is unlikely to occur.

German:
