English:
This is wrong. My January 15, 1986, declaration is well known around the world. I addressed a reduction in weapons, including nuclear weapons, and decided that no country should be in possession of nuclear weapons by 2000. I felt a personal, moral responsibility to end the stockpile of weapons. But Chernobyl opened my eyes like no other event: it showed me the terrible consequences of nuclear power, even if it is used for non-military purposes. It now showed me much more clearly what could happen if a nuclear bomb exploded. According to experts, a SS-18 missile could contain hundreds of Chernobyls.

German:
