English:
To be sure, the world has seen progress in some areas in recent decades. Girls’ education has improved, and in some areas the gender gap has narrowed. Despite aid and the recurrence of malaria and tuberculosis, life expectancy has increased in much of the world thanks to improved public health systems. Overall, however, the gaps in inequality are large, and in many cases they are growing.

German:
