English:
Although most Egyptians likely support Morsi’s goals, a dramatic expansion of the president’s powers to achieve them was a step too far for many. Given Egypt’s extreme polarization and mistrust between Islamic and secular forces, Morsi should have been anticipated to protest. After all, mistrust toward the powerful has been one of the pillars of the revolution. Another is a “zero-sum” attitude: any achievement by Morsi is perceived by his opponents as a loss.

German:
