English:
These interests include a new oil pipeline linking Myanmar and Kunming, capital of Yunnan Province. China is also working on “networking” projects – including railway lines and highways – to promote economic and social ties between China and ASEAN countries. The Myitsone Bridge construction stoppage and the Mekong River spillover have now cast a shadow over these projects, stoking fears of a chain reaction that could destroy China’s long-standing efforts to achieve greater regional integration.

German:
