English:
Such appeasement carries a price. It is clear in Islamabad, where, after a state order shut down Kalaschina’s dozen illegal mosques and seminars during the last two months, a frightened student protests against the government erupted. The angered students first surrendered to the government, then to the government. In a dramatic twist, Musharraf’s minister for religious affairs, the son of former dictator General Zia ul-Haq, promised to rebuild the damaged mosques, and even symbolically laid the first stone on one of them.

German:
