English:
My long road to unrest began more than a half-century ago. It was July 1945, some months after I returned from the concentration camp in Transnistria. That Paradise summer, I lived in a small Moldovan village, overwhelmed by the wonderful banality of a normal, safe environment. That afternoon was perfect, quiet, and still, laden with the moonlight of the space. I was alone in the universe, listening to a voice that was my and not mine. My companion was a book about Romanian mythology, it had a hard green partner, and it was given to me a few days before I reached the celebratory age of 9 years.

