English:
The Hartwell Group proposes to define three basic climate-change goals: ensuring safe and affordable energy sources for everyone (which should include alternatives to fossil fuels). Second, ensuring that economic development does not cause devastating environmental damage (not only reducing CO2 emissions, but also reducing indoor air pollution through burning biomes, reducing oceans, and protecting forests). Third, ensuring that we can deal with all kinds of climate change – manmade or natural – effectively (so that we finally recognize the importance of adaptation to climate change).

German:
