English:
A reasonable guess is that these two factors cancel. Thus, the expected real return on equity in a diversified portfolio of US stocks is now likely to be between 6% and 7%. The likely market return is this amount plus/minus the likely changes in valuation conditions: Will the share price rise or fall due to rising or falling price growth? Again, one can reasonably guess that these two factors can cancel out, say. Compare 6% to 7% return on equity with 1.25% return on bonds.

German:
