English:
The late Rinus Michels, also known as the “General” and the trainer of the Dutch team that lost narrowly to Germany in the 1974 final, famously said, “football is war.” When the Dutch took on Germany in 1988 and sprinted to become the next European champion, more people danced in the country’s streets than on the day the real war ended in May 1945.

