English:
What could have caused the glacier’s retreat to be stopped? One factor could be snow accumulations of dust and debris (falling under the smelting action of “aerosole”) on snow, which can increase the melting rate significantly upon accumulations of 400 grams per square meter. Between 400 and 600 grams has no effect, but if 600 grams are exceeded, the accumulations act as a protection against sun exposure and slow the meltdown.

