English:
Moreover, there would be serious consequences long before it. It is highly unlikely that Iran would simply succumb to a US or Israeli military strike. Instead, it would be expected to backfire by attacking US forces in Afghanistan and Iraq, launching terrorist attacks in regional and global cities, and bribing the flow of tankers through the Straits of Hormuz. The last thing the global economy needs is a barrel of oil at $200,000, but that could be the result.

