English:
This will help China attract more investors who want to diversify their portfolios. Chinese government bonds will become a significant global asset, and this should enable China’s private sector to finance on reasonable terms, while the US Federal Reserve’s prerogative over setting global monetary policy would probably diminish. The decades-long transition to a multi-polar world of production could thus lead to a more multi-polar world of currencies, with the renminbi as a major player.

