English:
NEW HAVEN – The Western foreign-policy experts have so far nurtured, with few exceptions, two distinct communities: the development community and the democratic community. For the most part, they had little or no in common: the development specialists dealt with dictatorships as well as democracies, and believed that prosperity could be best cultivated by focusing exclusively on economic issues and institutions.

German:
Aber das Hauptproblem besteht darin, dass die Investitionsquote des öffentlichen Sektors weiterhin unterhalb eines wachstumsstabilisierenden Niveaus liegt. Die Hauptschwierigkeit dabei, potenzielles Wachstum vollständig zu realisieren, besteht darin, die Zusammensetzung der Inlandsnachfrage vom Konsum hin zu Investitionen zu verschieben, ohne den Fremdkapitalanteil zu erhöhen. Dies heißt, dass der öffentliche Sektor dafür zahlt – in Form von Steuern und einer Verringerung des Haushaltskonsums (sowie des Vermögensaufbaus).
English:
But the main problem is that the public sector’s investment rate remains below a growth-stabilizing level. The key to fully achieving potential growth is shifting domestic demand from consumption to investment without raising the external capital ratio. That means that the public sector is paying for it – in the form of taxes and a reduction in household consumption (as well as asset building).

